sql:
SELECT MAX(fantasy_points) AS max_fantasy_points
FROM players
WHERE team = 'SF';

external_knowledge:
- "seasoned warriors" refers to players who have played in multiple games;
- "battles" refers to the games they have participated in;
- "strength of their team's collective spirit" refers to the average implied team total for the games played by the player;
- "guiding light" indicates that the results are ordered by the average implied team total in descending order.

- "top 3 players based on fantasy points" refers to the players who rank 1st, 2nd, or 3rd within their team based on the highest fantasy points scored;
- "average implied team total" is the mean of the implied team totals for all games involving players from that team;
- "average fantasy points" is the mean of the fantasy points scored by all players from that team.

- Teams with more than 30 players are considered large teams;
- A total salary exceeding 10 million indicates a high-spending team;
- An average projected weekly points greater than 10 suggests players with above-average performance expectations.

- "Star players" refer to the top-ranked players in each team based on fantasy points;
- "Lit up the scoreboard" means players with a high total implied team total;
- "Shining in more than 5 games" means players who have played more than 5 games.

